bib_record.title: Investigation of the production of the therapeutic radioisotope In-114m through proton and deuteron induced nuclear reactions on cadmium

free_txt: CGR-560 cyclotron
CGR-560 cyclotron
Stacked targets containing enriched and natural Cd
foils and Ti, Fe, Cu foils for monitoring and energy
degradation. Irradiation was done in Faraday-cup target
holder with 36, 33 and 16 MeV proton, 21 MeV deuteron
energies at VUB. One stack containing 4 foils was
irradiated with 9.1 MeV incident proton beam in
Kharkiv.
HPGe and Ge(Li) detectors were used. Nuclear data were
taken from NUDAT.
Stopping and energy degradation were calculated using
the Andersen-Ziegler polynomial approximation.

microns Al were used in Kharkiv.
